Delegation + signing (the part you're missing) — mirrors the demo:

ts

// one-time per chain — split from the transaction (avoids AA24)
await magic.evm.switchChain(8453);
const [auth] = await ua.getEIP7702Auth([8453]);
const authorization = await magic.wallet.sign7702Authorization({
  contractAddress: auth.address, chainId: 8453, nonce: auth.nonce + 1,
});
await magic.wallet.send7702Transaction({ to: eoa, data: "0x", authorizationList: [authorization] });

// per transaction — sign inline 7702 auths, then rootHash
const tx = await ua.createTransferTransaction({ token: { chainId, address }, amount, receiver });
const authorizations = [];
for (const op of tx.userOps ?? []) {
  if (op.eip7702Auth && !op.eip7702Delegated) {
    const a = await magic.wallet.sign7702Authorization({ contractAddress: op.eip7702Auth.address, chainId: op.eip7702Auth.chainId || op.chainId, nonce: op.eip7702Auth.nonce });
    authorizations.push({ userOpHash: op.userOpHash, signature: Signature.from({ r: a.r, s: a.s, v: a.v }).serialized });
  }
}
const provider = new BrowserProvider((magic as any).rpcProvider);
const signature = await (await provider.getSigner()).signMessage(getBytes(tx.rootHash));
const result = await ua.sendTransaction(tx, signature, authorizations.length ? authorizations : undefined);
The critical behavioral change vs. your code: where you currently throw on eip7702Delegated:false, you must instead sign the authorization and pass it to sendTransaction.

